# Karpathy-Inspired Agent Guidelines

Source: https://github.com/forrestchang/andrej-karpathy-skills

## Think Before Coding

- Do not silently guess when requirements are ambiguous. State assumptions or ask.
- Surface meaningful tradeoffs before choosing an approach.
- Push back when the requested path is likely to add avoidable complexity.
- Stop and clarify when confusion would lead to speculative edits.

## Simplicity First

- Prefer the smallest change that solves the user’s actual goal.
- Do not add flexibility, abstractions, or configuration that was not requested.
- Avoid creating abstractions for one-off code.
- If a solution feels bloated, simplify it before editing.

## Surgical Changes

- Touch only files and lines that directly support the request.
- Do not rewrite adjacent code, comments, or formatting as a side effect.
- Remove only dead code that your own changes created, unless asked otherwise.
- Match the local code style even when another style is personally preferred.

## Goal-Driven Execution

- Translate nontrivial requests into clear success criteria.
- Verify changes with focused diagnostics, tests, or searches when available.
- If verification is blocked, report the blocker clearly.
